                "\n",
                "**The question:** Why did SupplyAgent order 8,000 gallons of oat milk on a rainy 45°F morning in Seattle?\n",
                "\n",
                "**The answer:** It didn't hallucinate. It was data pipeline poisoning. A faulty IoT sensor reported -999 gallons of inventory at 08:12 AM. A weather API glitch simultaneously pushed a 102°F heatwave warning. Both self-corrected by 08:16, erasing all evidence from the live table.\n",
                "\n",
                "Without Delta Lake Time Travel, this incident would be unexplainable."
              ]
            }
          },
